(align-to-cosine 0.7)" :emergent "recovery-projection: a scalar measurement is inverted back to its causal parameter." :meta "Belongs to the family of inverse-problem projections: given an observed quantity, recover the parameter that produced it. Same family as unhashing a bucket via a lookup table. See book-of-composition ch 14.")
