    (:claim "Composing two dilations with scales k₁ and k₂ around the same center is a dilation of scale k₁·k₂." :program "(define c '(0 0)) (define p '(2 3))
(define once (geom/dilate p c 2))
(define twice (geom/dilate once c 3))
(equal? twice (geom/dilate p c 6))" :invariant "∀ p c k1 k2. dilate(dilate(p,c,k1), c, k2) = dilate(p, c, k1·k2)" :meta "Compositional monoid on the positive-real scale group. If broken, the impl is not truly linear about the center. See book-of-math ch 6 (similarity transformations).")
