    :runs "spec-only"
   
    (:claim "For any right triangle (a,b,hyp,angle) that satisfies the invariants, solve-right returns consistent values." :program "(define r (geom/solve-right '(:opp 3 :adj 4)))
(< (abs (- (list-ref r 1) 5)) 0.01)" :invariant "for any two consistent parameters, solve-right(p,q) returns (a,b,hyp,angle) satisfying a²+b²=hyp² and tan(angle)=a/b" :meta "Invariance under the Pythagorean and SOHCAHTOA identities. If broken, one derived value is out of sync. See book-of-math ch 4-5.")
    (:eng "If the invariant fails at runtime, that is a fault log line — the pure algebra should hold; a break implies the impl regressed." :math "The invariant is the closed-form algebraic identity that defines the verb's essence; falsification by counterexample is what makes it engineering-grade math." :cs "The runnable check is a property test in the sense of QuickCheck; make it a smoke test in CI so regressions are caught before ship."))
